3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bluefin calculates funding rates hourly using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and mark prices. The rate is applied to notional position size, with longs paying shorts when rates are positive. Settlement occurs precisely on the hour with automatic position adjustments. Sui's sub-second finality ensures immediate funding transfers without typical blockchain delays."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BONK","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK's meme coin status drives extreme sentiment swings that create persistent funding rate imbalances. High retail participation leads to crowded long positions during rallies, generating consistent positive funding rates. The pair's mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity while avoiding the compressed spreads of major pairs that reduce arbitrage profits."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK/USDT funding rates on Bluefin exhibit strong directional bias during trend periods, often sustaining 0.01-0.05% hourly rates for days. Meme coin cycles create predictable patterns where initial pump phases generate extreme positive funding as retail investors pile into longs. Rate normalization typically occurs during consolidation phases when speculative interest wanes. Weekend periods often show lower funding volatility due to reduced Sui ecosystem activity compared to weekdays."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities Structure"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange funding arbitrage works effectively between Bluefin and CEX platforms due to BONK's listing on major exchanges. Bluefin's hourly settlements versus 8-hour cycles elsewhere create temporal arbitrage windows. The DEX premium during high volatility periods offers additional profit layers beyond pure funding rate capture. Sui's fast finality enables quick hedging adjustments that are crucial for meme coin volatility management."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK's extreme price volatility can overwhelm funding rate profits if not properly hedged through delta-neutral strategies. Bluefin's limited liquidity during Sui network congestion poses execution risks for large positions. Smart contract risks inherent to DEX trading require position sizing considerations beyond traditional perpetual futures. Meme coin delisting risks, though currently low for BONK, represent tail risk scenarios that could trap positions."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Bluefin's hourly funding settlement affect BONK arbitrage strategies?","answer":"Hourly settlements provide more frequent profit realization compared to 8-hour cycles on CEXs, allowing for tighter risk management. This creates arbitrage opportunities by capturing funding differentials more frequently, especially important given BONK's volatile funding rate swings."},{"question":"What makes BONK funding rates more profitable than major cryptocurrencies on Bluefin?","answer":"BONK's meme coin status creates persistent funding rate imbalances due to retail sentiment-driven positioning. Unlike major cryptocurrencies with efficient arbitrage, BONK maintains higher absolute funding rates for extended periods during trend phases."},{"question":"How does Sui blockchain performance impact BONK/USDT funding rate strategies?","answer":"Sui's sub-second finality enables rapid position adjustments crucial for meme coin volatility management. Fast settlement reduces timing risks between funding calculations and hedging executions, improving strategy reliability compared to slower blockchain networks."},{"question":"What liquidity considerations affect large BONK funding rate positions on Bluefin?","answer":"BONK's mid-tier volume provides adequate liquidity for most retail strategies but may cause slippage for institutional-sized positions. During high volatility periods, bid-ask spreads can widen significantly, requiring careful execution timing to preserve arbitrage profits."}]}]
